title: For Sale/Trade:  1985 BMW 528e
postcontent:
I'm going to be moving August 1 and this can't come with us.
Let's be honest, this '85 Beemer is showing its age, but it does run and drive and we have the title.  It isn't our daily driver, but it usually gets around town once or twice a week.  We recently put in a new battery and it has two new tires, the spare is on the passenger side in the photos (it's full sized) and the regular tire is in the trunk. We've replaced most of the big stuff over the years, including the transmission, so it should just be the small things left.  It has the original engine, though, which is classic German engineering. It occasionally dies while idling, but that never happened before the new battery so it's most likely a loose connection somewhere.The back of the drivers seat has come off, but all parts are present, so someone more mechanically inclined than me should have no trouble reassembling it. There's a small dent in the front passenger side panel where someone slid into it a few winters ago. That being said, this beast is solid and you can see everything in those massive windows. Most electrical parts work perfectly, the power locks are slow to respond but do function. AC works when it feels like it but the heater was great last winter. Might be useful for parts or a project, it's up to you. We are moving and will only need one vehicle. This has been an occasional driver over the last two years. 
Odometer says 170403, not sure it's accurate. 
Automatic, power everything, leather interior, CD player with an auxiliary (I don't know how to use it, though)

**Last week we had a safety inspection done and the vehicle failed on one fault.  There is a leak somewhere in the power steering system.  We had this vehicle listed on Craigslist for $1300, and our mechanic said that a worst case scenario fix for the leak would be about $400, so we've dropped the price to $800.

Interceptor Base Vest Outershell, Cod Piece (official nomenclature... giggle) and neck guard. Unicor Interceptor IOTV Military Contract Kevlar Vest - . Size Medium for a 37-41" chest but fits a little large on myself, who usually clocks in at a 42". Contract overrun when the military requested the kidney plates and different drag tags. I bought these from a Security Contractor who's contract never materialized for some reason. These were still in the wrapper when I got them, and I modeled them (quite sexily, I might add) once for my old lady.
